-- Croatia’s Sisak May Get 100 Million-Euro Loan, Poslovni Reports
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-11-30T13:44:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-30/croatia-s-sisak-may-get-100-million-euro-loan-poslovni-reports.html
Croatian iron mill CMC Sisak d.o.o.,
a unit of Italy’s  Danieli SpA (DAN) , may get a 50 million-euro ($65
million) loan from the  European Bank of Reconstruction and
Development ,  Poslovni Dnevnik  reported, citing Zsuzsana
Hargitai, the head of the EBRD in Zagreb.  The plant also may get another 50 million-euro loan from
the  International Finance Corp ., the Zagreb-based business
newspaper reported, without saying how it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  